      "description": "Principles: Least astonishment, Consistency/Integrity.\n\nEvidence:\n- path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts:1-6 :: the top-of-file invariant says the wrapper only injects `--json` plus an extension-managed `--session` when appropriate.\n- path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts:787-790 :: buildExecutionPlan also injects `--user-agent` when the ChatGPT headless compatibility workaround applies.\n- path: test/agent-browser.test.ts:670-711 :: the test suite explicitly verifies that `--user-agent` injection behavior.\n- workflow: npm run verify :: the compatibility-workaround tests pass, confirming the comment is stale rather than the code being wrong.\n\nWhy it matters: this header is supposed to be the local contract for reviewers reading the runtime module. Right now it understates real behavior that materially changes launched CLI args.\n\nMinimal proposed fix: update the purpose header and nearby invariant text so it reflects the current compatibility-workaround injection behavior without overstating the wrapper's scope.\n\nAcceptance criteria: the runtime header accurately describes current injected-argument behavior, including the narrow compatibility case; no contradictory comments remain nearby; `npm run verify` still passes.",
